where the polarizability is given by (sum-over-states)
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\left[\alpha_{fi}\left(\omega_{I}\right)\right]_{\rho\lambda}=-\sum_{k}\sum_{n}\left[\frac{\left\langle \psi_{f}\right|\mu_{ik,\rho}\left|\psi_{k,n}\right\rangle \left\langle \psi_{k,n}\right|\mu_{ki,\lambda}\left|\psi_{i}\right\rangle }{\varepsilon_{i}+\hbar\omega_{I}-\varepsilon_{kn}+i\hbar\gamma}+\frac{\left\langle \psi_{f}\right|\mu_{ik,\lambda}\left|\psi_{k,n}\right\rangle \left\langle \psi_{n}\right|\mu_{ki,\rho}\left|\psi_{i}\right\rangle }{\varepsilon_{i}-\hbar\omega_{S}-\varepsilon_{kn}+i\hbar\gamma}\right].
\]

\end_inset

